# Tokens

Pathogen currently exposes Tailwind-compatible `primary-*` and `neutral-*` colour aliases. Components should move toward semantic roles on top of those aliases so implementation code describes intent instead of choosing raw colour stops.

## Existing Theme Contract

- `--font-sans` is Inter-first: `"Inter", "Avenir Next", "Segoe UI", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif`.
- `--font-mono` is a standard UI monospace stack.
- `--color-primary-*` defaults to Tailwind blue.
- `--color-neutral-*` defaults to Tailwind slate.
- Host apps may override `--color-primary-*`.

## Recommended Semantic Colour Roles

These roles should become the preferred language for components and previews. The swatches show Pathogen's current default theme values; host applications may map the same roles to different brand values.

