```

Use `--pvc-color-accent` and `--pvc-color-accent-strong` for text, borders, and outline controls on a surface. Use `--pvc-color-accent-solid` and `--pvc-color-accent-solid-hover` for filled primary actions. In dark mode, foreground accents stay lighter for contrast on dark surfaces; solid fills stay saturated so primary buttons remain confident.

## Type Scale Use

```css
--type-meta: 0.75rem;      /* 12px: metadata, hints */
--type-control: 0.875rem;  /* 14px: controls, labels, dense UI */
--type-body: 1rem;         /* 16px: body copy */
--type-section: 1.25rem;   /* 20px: section headings */
--type-page: 1.9375rem;    /* 31px: page headings */
```

Use `14px` and `16px` as the product workhorses. Use larger sizes sparingly in real application surfaces.

Guidance:

- Treat `12px`, `14px`, and `16px` as the default product system.
- Use `20px` for section-level hierarchy when it improves scanning.
- Reserve the page heading size for true page ownership, not preview decoration.
- Keep typography geometric and direct: short labels, consistent alignment, and restrained weights.

## Radius

```css
--pvc-radius-control-sm: 0.125rem; /* tight form primitives */
--pvc-radius-control: 0.25rem;     /* compact controls */
--pvc-radius-action: 0.375rem;     /* buttons, tabs, grouped controls */
--pvc-radius-panel: 0.5rem;        /* data grids and larger panels */
```

Guidance:

- Form primitives: `2px` to `4px`.
- Buttons, tabs, links focus shapes, and inputs: `4px` to `6px`.
- Data grids and grouped component frames: `6px` to `8px`.
- Prefer sharper corners for dense clinical workflows; use softer corners only when grouping a larger surface.
- Large preview and docs containers should avoid `xl` and `2xl`.

## Elevation

```css
--pvc-shadow-none: none;
--pvc-shadow-overlay: 0 1px 3px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2);
```

Guidance:

- Base product surfaces: no shadow.
- Grouped surfaces: border plus subtle background difference.
- Overlays, tooltips, popovers, and menus: small shadow.
- Avoid `shadow-lg` in product examples.

## Geometry And Composition

Use geometry through layout before decoration:

- Strong vertical and horizontal alignment.
- Clear gutters between primary and secondary work areas.
- Dividers, table rules, and borders that describe real structure.
- Small accent bars or blocks only for navigation, selection, focus, status, or meaningful grouping.
- Asymmetric compositions only when the workflow has asymmetric priority.

## Motion

```css
--pvc-duration-fast: 120ms;
--pvc-duration-default: 160ms;
--pvc-duration-overlay: 200ms;
```

Use colour, border, background, and opacity transitions before movement. Reserve scale/fade for overlays.
